{
  "stem": "20089.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the GIs, of course, weren't allowed at that stage to fraternize with the-- with the German Frauleins.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was against-- it was against the law, the American law.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So any young girl was very much in demand.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I was young at the time, one of the youngest.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "In fact, I was the youngest at-- in-- in UNRRA and in AJDC.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I was able to get almost anything I wanted because I was a female and-- and they were interested in-- in taking girls out.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I managed to get a fully equipped gymnasium from the American Army.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they actually transported all the equipment to Rosenheim Camp.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that was a tremendous, tremendous boon for the young children.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I've never seen anything like it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Do you remember some of the GIs?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, except they were GIs and probably 23, 24.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were in the American Army of Occupation because Germany was then occupied.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I must say that I didn't come from a religious home, so my knowledge of the Jewish festivals was limited.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But one of the-- one of the great moments of my life in that camp was the first Pesach Seder that took place at Rosenheim after the war.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was 194-- 47, because I arrived in-- in Munich in July of '46.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So in April, March-April '47, it was the first time that these children were able to have a Pesach Seder.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And the person who was taking the Seder, the person who was invited by the AJDC and the Jewish Agency, was a Palestinian man who was rather important in Palestine at the time by the name of Nachum Levine.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I remember his name.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I quite clearly remember his face.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
